tle> A Conversation With Blaze</span><hr size=1> *Walks with solemnity through the gates of Ancient Erudin*  *Manifests his presence in the Sacred Place*  *Looks to the heavens and then bows his head, shedding a single tear from each eye*  *Extends each arm around the astral forms of the essences of those of Aquilo past and Di Arcis present that have been willed to form next to him*  *Sits down and begins to focus his chi as each fist glows with a bright orange fury*<br>
<br>
Blaze, hear my call to you father.  I come before you seeking intervention.  Has too much time passed for my words and council to matter?  Am I too far removed from the lives they lead here to be a catalyst for positive change?  Whatever the case may be, the fates willed long ago that I am duty bound to serve as an advocate for those who be troubled, whether they value my input or not.<br>
<br>
The mortals of each family have lost their focus Great Phoenix.  They have strayed yet again into the outer realms of building frustration and blurred visions of contentment.  What can be done when so much has been rended and one's clarity of purpose has divided from the other's?  Is it your will that each is destined to dismiss the more powerful ties that bind long term?  I think not, so I come to you now to plea for intervention.<br>
<br>
Speak to their hearts Holy Bird of Flame.  Remind them once again of their heritage and of the sacrifices of those who came before.  The foundation must not be allowed to wither, for it is a foundation meant to last for all ages.  The simple truths that are so easily lost when strife affirms its renewed presence must not be ignored.<br>
<br>
Visions come and go within the gaming context.  Guild dynamics and formations shift as do the sands of time.  Life circumstances dictate interest, commitment, sustained commonality.  The life span of a specific grouping is finite, no matter what the intentions are of its founders.  What then are we to internalize from this established norm and mandated principle?  I submit that we must make them see once more with eyes of compassion and humility.  Only then will clarity be given the opportunity to surface once more and reclaim its dominance.<br>
<br>
I proffer the supposition that communication that relies solely on the format of text-based interaction lacks vital ingredients that make accurate interpretations possible.  We all speak a language that is dependent on demonstrative gestures and inflection to assist the other party in truly understanding the subtleties of any message being conveyed.  When those aspects are lacking, one cannot help but risk the possibility of being misunderstood.  Perhaps at times not in substance, but certainly at the very least in severity and presentation of sentiment.<br>
<br>
The combination of these characteristics makes it impossible to formulate an intact interaction that gives hope its best chance to succeed.  It therefore falls to each individual to value the other individuals he or she is surrounded by.  Harsh words exchanged in this medium only waste time.  They are not relevant in the greater chain of being anyway.<br>
<br>
Blaze, help them find their focus once more.  It is not the arbitrary and fleeting moments of perceived membership in something imaginary that engenders ultimate meaning for those who enjoy the fantasy realm.  It does not matter in the grand scheme of things why you feel the way you do or what prompted it or what impact it will have in the short term.  Friendship is what matters.  Friendship is what must endure.  Friendship must be the ultimate purpose behind engaging in such an exercise if it is to have meaning.<br>
<br>
Sometimes friends go through periods of difficulty.  Sometimes friends doubt the conviction of their bonds.  Sometimes friends say things they end up regretting.  The important thing is, friends always end up realizing that the source of what gave them commonality is strong enough to withstand the tests of time.  Foolish and petty arguments over what one group desires out of the gaming environment as opposed to the other is unseemly at best.<br>
<br>
It falls to all parties involved to evaluate the larger issue.  If you genuinely care about each other, then disagreement over something that is ultimately trivial will not hinder your ability to maintain relationships.  That should be the point that drives and motivates everyone's actions at all times.  If it isn't the case, then the friendship you had ends up being superficial and won't be missed when gone.<br>
<br>
Go your separate ways if you must, but be mindful of doing so with grace and caring for the other's perspective and point of view.  Believe and trust that each side has a merited point of view and that the friendships forged over such a long period cannot be so casually dismissed.  I weep for all involved who genuinely feel hurt and are experiencing dismay.  If it matters, make the effort to not lose touch with those you care about.<br>
<br>
Blaze and I will be with all of you no matter what path you follow.  Good people are good people because they are good people.  That doesn't automatically change overnight because of separation.  Send to me your mystical muse father.  I invoke The Calling.<br>
<br>
*Stands and kneels before the Great Bard of Flame known as The Calling*  *Channels the melody and words of his great song into the astral forms now imbued with the Light's own Flame*  *The Calling sings:  &quot;Wherever You Will Go&quot;*<br>
